title: Faruk Sabanci Feat. Jaren - Discover (Remixes) 2013 (320kbps) (A
description:
Faruk Sabanci Feat. Jaren - Discover (Remixes) 2013 

              Trance, Hard Dance, Progressive, Dubstep | Arisa Audio 

            320 kbps | MP3 | unmixed | 2013-09-02 | 00:48:44 | 115 Mb




One of the driving forces in this new era of Trance artists is 21 year-old Faruk Sabanci. He's teamed up with Jaren for the already well-received 'Discover'. Rising high in the Beatport Charts as well as being exclusively premiered by Armin van Buuren, this future-classic has already been set for immortality from the get-go. On this day we here at Arisa Audio establishments are quite proud to present this huge Multi-Genre Remix package. We've step outside to box and have swung our doors wide open for styles new to this branch! First up is US-based talent Austin Collins, better known as Au5. With a career that has been on the up, this talent has already caught the eye of influential artists such as Skrillex and BT to mention a few. Au5 puts a melodic Dubstep take on the spread. Not for the faint hearted! Next up is Dutch maestro Rafael Frost; with his previous Arisa Audio outing gaining global support from the likes of Armin van Buuren, Ferry Corsten, Porter Robinson and much much more, Frost takes another step and delivers a massive Big Room Prog-Trance stormer. Another pleaser for the Trancers is brought to you by Uplifting Trance sensation Photographer as he shifts it into 6th gear and delivers a peak-time weapon made for destruction! The package continues with a BLASTING Hardstyle remix by Italian producer The R3belz. Already premiered by Headhunterz, The R3belz takes things to the next level to expose a completely different side of 'Discover' you never could've seen coming. We continue to welcome fresh and new talent as expose Dutch producer, Revero. Fresh off his remix for Tiesto's Ultra Anthem, this talent puts a splendid Big Room House take on the table teleporting you back to the biggest Summer Festivals! Having his WORLDWIDE debut is brand new talent hailing from the heart of Russia, please lets give a warm welcome to, Reunify. Keeping the melodic essence of the Original, Reunify comes along with an elegant Melodic House remix as he boost balearic vibes. Stepping outside the box once again, the first Deep House outing on Arisa Audio is provided by Turkish producer Sezer Uysal who smoothens things up with his fantastic rendition injected with a chunk of groove. Last but certainly not least is IDMA nominee Zetandel who provides an angelic Chillout take to complete the package. Enjoy!
